Manchester United Leads Chelsea 2-1 in Second Half of Premier League Game

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-05-08T16:41:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/manchester-united-leads-2-0-against-chelsea-in-england-s-premier-league.html
Manchester United  leads defending
champion Chelsea 2-1 in today’s match between the top two teams
in English soccer’s Premier League.  Javier Hernandez  got United's
first goal in the opening minute at Old Trafford, Nemanja Vidic
adding a second in the 23rd.  Frank Lampard  scored for Chelsea in the 68th minute.  United leads the standings on 73 points, while Chelsea has
70 and would go top on goal difference with a victory. There are
two rounds of games after today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  